com.github.dm.jrt.android.core.invocation

Class TargetInvocationFactory<IN,OUT>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.dm.jrt.android.core.invocation.TargetInvocationFactory<IN,OUT>
  • Type Parameters:
    IN - the input data type.
    OUT - the output data type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Parcelable

    public abstract class TargetInvocationFactory<IN,OUT>
extends Object
implements Parcelable
    Class representing a context invocation factory target.

    Note that, in case a class not representing a ContextInvocation is passed to the factory, the specified invocation class will be passed as the first argument to a special context invocation in order to be automatically instantiated via reflection.
    The latter class will inherit from ContextInvocationWrapper.
    It is possible to avoid that, by creating a target invocation factory of a common invocation by defining a specialized class like: 

         

         public class MyInvocationWrapper<IN, OUT>
                 extends ContextInvocationWrapper<IN, OUT> {

             public MyInvocationWrapper(final String arg) {

                 super(new MyInvocation<IN, OUT>(arg));
             }
         }

    Created by davide-maestroni on 08/20/2015.
